Empire of the Air: The Men Who Made Radio is a documentary film on the history of the old-time radio. It was directed by Ken Burns in 1991. The film first aired on January 29, 1992. It was narrated by actor Jason Robards. The film focused primarily on three pioneers of radio in America; David Sarnoff, Lee DeForest, and Edwin Armstrong.
